Bundled sidecar binaries (macOS DMG distribution)

The PortBay app bundle ships the following unmodified third-party executables
as sidecars. They are separate programs invoked as subprocesses — an aggregate
distribution, not a combined work — and each remains under its own license.
Binaries are fetched/built at pinned versions with SHA-256 verification by the
scripts/fetch-*.sh scripts.

  Caddy 2.10.2 (with caddy-dns/cloudflare v0.2.3)
      License: Apache-2.0 — https://github.com/caddyserver/caddy

  dnsmasq 2.92
      License: GPL-2.0 or GPL-3.0 (dual-licensed; PortBay distributes it
      under GPL-3.0). Upstream: https://thekelleys.org.uk/dnsmasq/
      Complete corresponding source for the pinned version is available
      from the upstream release archive; the build/fetch recipe is
      scripts/fetch-dnsmasq.sh.

  mkcert 1.4.4
      License: BSD-3-Clause — https://github.com/FiloSottile/mkcert

  Mailpit 1.30.0
      License: MIT — https://github.com/axllent/mailpit

  cloudflared 2025.11.1
      License: Apache-2.0 — https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared

  process-compose 1.110.0
      License: Apache-2.0 — https://github.com/F1bonacc1/process-compose

The portbay-hosts-helper and portbay-mcp sidecars are first-party PortBay
code (AGPL-3.0-only, this repository). Optional managed runtimes (e.g.
PHP-FPM) are downloaded on demand from the portbay-runtimes project, which
carries its own license attribution.

  portbay-agent
      PortBay's local-model agent engine is derived from Cline CLI / SDK
      (https://github.com/cline/cline), pinned from the Apache-2.0 upstream
      fork maintained at https://github.com/portbay-app/portbay-cline.
      Copyright 2026 Cline Bot Inc. PortBay modifications are copyright
      Tribal House and PortBay contributors. The fork's LICENSE is Apache-2.0;
      no upstream NOTICE file was present at the pinned source.

